# delphai react app

delphai react frontend repository.

# Setup
- Prerequisite - Node.js
   - [Debian and Ubuntu based](https://github.com/nodesource/distributions/blob/master/README.md#debinstall)
   - [Mac and windows](https://nodejs.org/en/download)

To run the app:
1. Install dependency using below command

```
yarn
```

2. Run the following command to start the app
```
yarn start
```

3. For testing this repository uses [jest](https://jestjs.io/) with [@testing-library/react](https://testing-library.com/docs/react-testing-library/intro). To test, run:
```
yarn test
```
you can also run jest in watch mode with
```
yarn test --watch
```
to update the snapshots run
```
yarn test -u
```

# Module resolution

For refering to `src/` you can use `@/`. So if you have a file located at `src/foo.tsx` you can use

```typescript
import foo from '@/foo'
```
